<h1>Help for Bang Wallpaper Plus</h1>

Bang Wallpaper Plus downloads the latest bing wallpaper automatically at startup. The wallpaper is then displayed on your desktop.

<p><strong>1. Bang Wallpaper Plus features</strong></p>
<ul> 
<li> Impressive wallpapers from bing®</li> 
<li> Wallpaper annotation including host info </li> 
<li> Runs without admin privileges </li> 
<li> Installs without admin privileges </li> 
<li> Runs at startup </li> 
<li> Works with proxies </li> 
<li> Tried and tested on Windows 7, Windows 8.1, and Windows 10</li> 
</ul>

<p><strong>2. Installation</strong></p>
Installation should be straight-forward and does not require admin privileges.
<ol>
<li>Download the executable. </li>
<li>Run the installer. </li>
<li>No admin priviledges should be required for installation. </li>
<li>Follow the instructions on the screen. </li>
<li>Upon completion, you are asked whether to run Bang Wallpaper Plus. </li>
</ol>

<p><strong>3. Uninstall</strong></p>
Bang Wallpaper Plus comes with an uninstall routine that runs without admin privileges.
<ol>
<li>Open the folder with Bang Wallpaper Plus on your computer. </li>
<li>Double-click on uninstall.exe. </li>
<li>Follow the instructions on the screen. </li>
</ol>

<p><strong>4. Settings</strong></p>
Bang Wallpaper Plus from version 1.1 displays a box with host information such as hostname, IP, username. You may disable
this feature as follows:
<ol>
<li>On your computer, press the start button. </li>
<li>Navigate to the programs and to Bang Wallpaper Plus. </li>
<li>Left-click on settings, a dialog with settings for Bang Wallpaper Plus will now open. </li>
<li>Uncheck the tick box display host info. </li>
<li>Press OK. </li>
<li>In the start menu folder left-click on Bang Wallpaper Plus.</li>
</ol>
You may as well change settings for Bang Wallpaper Plus by editing a configuration file. The procedure works as follows:
<ol>
<li>Open the folder with Bang Wallpaper Plus on your computer. </li>
<li>Right-click on the file bang.ini. </li>
<li>Open bang.ini with an editor (such as notepad or wordpad). </li>
<li>If you want to dispense with host information, the entry in the line hostinfo=yes will have to change to hostinfo=no. </li>
<li>If you look for an alternate image source, the entry in the line source=bing will have to change to source=heise. Note that heise as an image source is considered experimental. </li>
<li>Save your changes.</li>
<li>Close the file bang.ini.</li>
<li>Your changes will take effect the next time you run Bang Wallpaper Plus.</li>
</ol>
